main.java.de.bsi.tsesimulator.utils.filefilters

Class LogmessageFileFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.java.de.bsi.tsesimulator.utils.filefilters.LogmessageFileFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.FileFilter

    public class LogmessageFileFilter
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.FileFilter
    Used to filter a directory for filenames ending with the extension ".log" and beginning with a String that can be specified. Used for filtering the storageDir for duplicates of LogMessages and adding the appropriate "_Fc-x" to their filename.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    dpottkaemper

      • LogmessageFileFilter

        public LogmessageFileFilter()
        Default constructor.

      • LogmessageFileFilter

        public LogmessageFileFilter(java.lang.String fileNameToBeFiltered)
        Constructor which sets the fileName that shall be used for filtering. File name String has to be present at the beginning of each file the filter is applied to if that file shall be selected by the filter.
        Example: if the fileName is foo then foo-123.log would be selected, but ffoo.log would not be.
        Parameters:
        fileNameToBeFiltered - - the new file name beginning that shall be applied by the filter.

      • setFileName

        public void setFileName(java.lang.String fileName)
        Has to be set every time BEFORE using this filter so that it matches only filenames that contain the specified file name and start with it.
        For example, if the fileName is set to "testFile" then testFile123.log and testFile.log would pass the filter but not test_File.log.
        Parameters:
        fileName - - the file name that should be filtered.
